definition: variant of 復|复[fu4]/to reply to a letter

sentences.english: It does not overwrite any cell-level information.
sentences.chinese: 它沒有覆蓋任何元級消息。

sentences.english: Histologically, dentigerous cysts are lined by stratified squamous nonkeratinizing epithelium.
sentences.chinese: 組織學上含齒囊腫爲多層鱗狀未角化上皮細胞所覆蓋。

sentences.english: We will accelerate the improvement of the social security system that covers both urban and rural residents.
sentences.chinese: 加快健全覆蓋城鄉居民的社會保障體系。

sentences.english: The percentage of soil moisture content and surface residual coverage jointly influence the quantity of wind erosion.
sentences.chinese: 土壤含水率和地表殘茬覆蓋共同影響着土壤的風蝕量。

sentences.english: Then using a special knife, they cut off the lids of the cells.

sentences.english: The article also explains how to override the default file creation location.
sentences.chinese: 這篇文章也說明了如何覆蓋默認的文件創建位置。

sentences.english: We have rewritten all the sample scripts to cover the new benchmark.
sentences.chinese: 我們已經重寫了所有示例腳本，以覆蓋新的基準。

sentences.english: The grip cover lies directly over the hammering end of the tool.
sentences.chinese: 抓地力覆蓋在於直接在錘打結束工具。

sentences.english: Safety of the spectators will also be guaranteed thanks to a related comprehensive insurance bill.

sentences.english: During that project, the new torch was carefully covered with thin sheets of 24k gold.

sentences.english: Heatmaps and overlays quickly provide perspective into user behavior and habits.

sentences.english: The pilots looked outside the cockpit window and saw that the plane was coated by a thin cloud.
sentences.chinese: 駕駛員注視座艙窗外，看到飛機被一層薄雲覆蓋。

sentences.english: Code coverage is a metric that reminds me of keeping track of your bad beats.

sentences.english: Lewis. A Mars rampant with life. A water-covered Venus populated with floating, living islands.

sentences.english: A network consisting of about 300,000 surveillance cameras covers the entire capital.
sentences.chinese: 30萬攝像頭組成的監控網絡覆蓋整座城市。
